often gathering enough energy to get through one hike, let alone multiple hikes. That’s why I will be combining biking and hiking during my time in Liechtenstein (or as locals would call it: “Velo-Hochtourismus”). That way I can incorporate some biking into my trips.

If you have other ideas about how to responsibly see Liechtenstein, go ahead and comment down below! All suggestions are welcome!

Hi Bogdan, I am really looking forward to your adventure(s) in Liechtenstein. Love the idea of Velo-Hochtourismus. Hiking and biking are definitely better for a climate conscious future than motorised travel.

One hiking tour that you should try is Schaftal, near Malbun in Malbunwald, where you can find all-native trees: Gipsophila, Mountain Pine, Alpine Kobold, and others. – There is a post about it here: Hallo Atlantic Adornment (link: https://www.summitsteps.eu/2020/01/christmas-hike-in-schaftal-alpine.html)

Please continue with the rebuilding of your bike and looking forward for your adventures in November. – Till then, all the best, Michael

Thank you Michael! I’ll be sure to check that out when the weather improves! For now I’ll continue on making my fixie even more fixie.

Looking forward to reading about your adventures!

Please let me know. Thank you
